summary: One thing I love about Peter is that he, like every other human on the planet, struggles to do what’s right.  He entertains the...
body: One thing I love about Peter is that he, like every other human on the planet, struggles to do what’s right. He entertains the thought of turning to a life of crime, but ultimately rejects it. He rarely succumbs to selfishness, but when he does, bad things tend to happen.

title: Real Talk
body:
Into The Spider Verse looks like a fun loving tribute to the Spider Man franchise, clearly made by fans who have nothing but love for the character. And what’s even more amazing? It feels like an honest to god love letter to the franchise and not a soulless nostalgia pandering cash grab.

Please go see this movie on opening weekend, I want to see it succeed and  because well, we need more Spider Man movies where Spider Man acts like Spider Man and not Tony Stark’s sidekick.
